bar"},"Contact-Us":{"id":"Contact-Us","title":"Contact Us","description":"If you have any issues with the Vincent SDK, general questions about Vincent, or specific feature requests, please post them on the official Vincent GitHub Repo.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"Developers/Custom-Tools":{"id":"Developers/Custom-Tools","title":"Custom Tools","description":"Vincent allows you to create custom tools for AI agents to interact with your application. This guide will show you how to define, implement, and secure custom tools.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"Developers/Quick-Start":{"id":"Developers/Quick-Start","title":"Quick Start Guide","description":"This guide will help you get started with the Vincent SDK for both browser and Node.js environments.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"Users/Onboarding":{"id":"Users/Onboarding","title":"Getting Started with Vincent","description":"Vincent allows you to securely delegate your wallet capabilities to AI agents. This guide will help you get started.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"Why-Vincent":{"id":"Why-Vincent","title":"Start Here","description":"Vincent is an open-source framework powered by Lit Protocol that empowers developers to create automated, user-controlled AI agents. With Vincent, you can build agents that automate the execution of operations across crypto networks, traditional finance (TradFi), and e-commerce platforms—all while ensuring users retain full control over their assets and data. Powered by Lit’s decentralized key management network and smart contracts, Vincent is your gateway to the future of the automated, User-Owned Web.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"}}}}